NNoottiicceess
       There are backup copies  of  the  Device  Database  files,
       which  have  the  same names as the Device Database files,
       except they are prefixed with a . (dot).  For example, the
       backup  copy  of  /etc/device.tab is /etc/.device.tab.  If
       the Device Database becomes corrupted it can  be  restored
       from the backup copies.

